COURSE DETAILS

This short course is aimed at introducing researchers to analysing
ecological and environmental data with Bayesian GLMs using R. Theory
underpinning Bayesian inference will be discussed, as well as analytical
methods and statistical interpretation. Sessions will be a blend of
interactive demonstrations and lectures, where learners will have the
opportunity to ask questions throughout. Prior to the course, attendees
will receive R script and datasets and a list of R packages to install.

By the end of the course, participants should be able to:

   - Recognise the distinction between frequentist and Bayesian approaches
   to model fitting
   - Apply data exploration techniques and avoid the common pitfalls in
   tackling a data analysis
   - Apply a 9-step protocol to fitting Bayesian GLMs
   - Understand and apply alternative approaches to model selection
   - Apply statistical modelling methods to ecological data using Bayesian
   GLMs



